<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,1142,1421]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1179,1205]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Remarks.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Penzes, Z. &amp; Tang, C. - T. &amp; Stone, G. N. &amp; Nicholls, J. A. &amp; Schweger, S. &amp; Bozso, M. &amp; Melika, G." box="[480,710,1179,1205]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="245 - 289" refId="ref49925" refString="Penzes, Z., Tang, C. - T., Stone, G. N., Nicholls, J. A., Schweger, S., Bozso, M. &amp; Melika, G. (2018) Current status of the oak gallwasp (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini) fauna of the Eastern Palaearctic and Oriental Regions. Zootaxa, 4433 (2), 245 - 289. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4433.2.2" type="journal article" year="2018">
Pénzes 
<emphasis box="[567,624,1179,1205]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H." box="[722,1022,1179,1205]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" refId="ref55993" refString="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H. (1996) Insect and mite galls of Japan in colors. Zenkoku-Nouson-Kyoukai, Tokyo, 826 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1996">Yukawa &amp; Masuda (1996)</bibRefCitation>
said that ‘ 
<bibRefCitation author="Monzen, K." box="[1139,1337,1178,1205]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="15 - 21" refId="ref48520" refString="Monzen, K. (1953) Revision of the Japanese gall wasps with the descriptions of new genus, subgenus, species and subspecies (I). Cynipidae (Cynipinae), Hymenoptera. Annual Reports of the Gakugei Faculty of the Iwate University, 5, 15 - 21." type="journal article" year="1953">Monzen’s (1953)</bibRefCitation>
description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Monzen" authorityYear="1953" box="[232,444,1215,1241]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblongus">
<emphasis box="[232,444,1215,1241]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Andricus oblongus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is actually an 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kovalev" authorityYear="1965" box="[606,846,1215,1241]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="symbioticus">
<emphasis box="[606,846,1215,1241]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Andricus symbioticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gall attacked by inquilines’. Therefore, they left this species as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kovalev" authorityYear="1965" box="[429,592,1251,1277]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="symbioticus">
<emphasis box="[429,592,1251,1277]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">A. symbioticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
even though they found 11 pins with adults thought to be of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Monzen" authorityYear="1953" box="[1274,1408,1251,1277]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblongus">
<emphasis box="[1274,1408,1251,1277]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">A. oblongus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Monzen’s collection (
<collectingRegion box="[393,465,1287,1313]" country="Japan" name="Kyoto" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Kyoto</collectingRegion>
University) that actually belong to a 
<taxonomicName box="[878,1075,1287,1313]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Synergus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[878,980,1287,1313]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Synergus</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Ide, T. &amp; Abe, Y." box="[1232,1432,1287,1313]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref44568" refString="Ide, T. &amp; Abe, Y. (2020) Cynipoidea. In: Editorial Committee of Catalogue of the Insects of Japan (Eds.), Catalogue of the Insects of Japan. Vol. 9. Hymenoptera (Part 2 Apocrita, Parasitica). Touka Shobo, Fukuoka, pp. 1 - 23. [in Japanese]" type="book chapter" year="2020">Ide &amp; Abe (2020)</bibRefCitation>
, the tribal placement of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Monzen" authorityYear="1953" box="[411,545,1323,1349]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblongus">
<emphasis box="[411,545,1323,1349]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">A. oblongus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName box="[580,678,1323,1349]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cynipini">Cynipini</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1896" box="[716,824,1323,1349]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Synergini">Synergini</taxonomicName>
should be revised in future.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,1142,1421]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1358,1384]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Biology.</emphasis>
The gall is recorded as forming masses on the bark of 
<taxonomicName box="[949,1067,1359,1385]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serrata">
<emphasis box="[949,1067,1359,1385]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Q. serrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sect. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Shinji" baseAuthorityYear="1943" box="[1148,1242,1359,1385]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1148,1242,1359,1385]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Monzen, K." box="[1269,1431,1358,1385]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="15 - 21" refId="ref48520" refString="Monzen, K. (1953) Revision of the Japanese gall wasps with the descriptions of new genus, subgenus, species and subspecies (I). Cynipidae (Cynipinae), Hymenoptera. Annual Reports of the Gakugei Faculty of the Iwate University, 5, 15 - 21." type="journal article" year="1953">Monzen 1953</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Penzes, Z. &amp; Tang, C. - T. &amp; Stone, G. N. &amp; Nicholls, J. A. &amp; Schweger, S. &amp; Bozso, M. &amp; Melika, G." box="[151,360,1395,1421]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="245 - 289" refId="ref49925" refString="Penzes, Z., Tang, C. - T., Stone, G. N., Nicholls, J. A., Schweger, S., Bozso, M. &amp; Melika, G. (2018) Current status of the oak gallwasp (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini) fauna of the Eastern Palaearctic and Oriental Regions. Zootaxa, 4433 (2), 245 - 289. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4433.2.2" type="journal article" year="2018">
Pénzes 
<emphasis box="[236,285,1395,1421]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
